# SiphonAI STIR/SHAKEN trust anchors — TEMPLATE, NOT A USABLE BUNDLE
# =================================================================
#
# This file is a PLACEHOLDER. As shipped it contains ZERO certificates,
# so pointing `[security.stir_shaken].trust_anchors` at it with
# `enabled = true` will FAIL AT STARTUP ("contains no PEM certificates").
# That is deliberate — SiphonAI will not run STIR/SHAKEN verification
# against an unpopulated anchor file.
#
# Replace everything below the marker with the authentic STI-PA trusted
# STI-CA root certificate(s) for your jurisdiction (see contrib/README.md),
# then copy this file into place (e.g. /etc/siphon-ai/sti-pa-roots.pem) and
# set:
#
#     [security.stir_shaken]
#     enabled       = true
#     trust_anchors = "/etc/siphon-ai/sti-pa-roots.pem"
#
# WHAT GOES HERE
# --------------
# The set of root CA certificates the Secure Telephone Identity Policy
# Administrator (STI-PA) publishes as trusted. In the US that list is
# operated by iconectiv; authorized service providers retrieve it from the
# STI-PA trust-list API (ATIS-1000080). It is the set of anchors a SHAKEN
# signing certificate's chain must terminate at to be trusted. It MAY
# contain more than one certificate, and it changes as STI-CAs are added or
# removed — re-fetch and update this file when the STI-PA list changes.
#
# We intentionally do NOT ship a baked-in root: a stale or wrong trust
# anchor is a security defect (it silently rejects every legitimately
# signed call, or — worse — could trust the wrong issuer). The authentic,
# current list must come from the authoritative source and be verified by
# fingerprint. See contrib/README.md for how to obtain and verify it.
#
# FORMAT
# ------
# Standard PEM. One or more concatenated certificate blocks. Lines outside
# the BEGIN/END markers (like these comments) are ignored by the parser, so
# you can keep notes inline. Order does not matter for anchors.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# PASTE THE AUTHENTIC STI-PA TRUSTED ROOT CERTIFICATE(S) BELOW THIS LINE
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
